# E-commerce System MVP – Product Manager Assignment (Answers)

## Part 1: Product Design

### 1. User Roles and Core Scenarios

| User Role | Core Scenarios |
|-----------|----------------|
| Customer | Browse products, search/filter, view product details, add to cart, place orders, make payments, view order history, request order cancellation |
| Operations Staff | Create/edit products, manage pricing & inventory, review orders, update order status (ship, complete, cancel) |
| Platform Admin | Manage user permissions, view platform data (orders, GMV), handle abnormal orders |

---

### 2. MVP Feature List and Priority

| Module | Feature | Priority | Reason |
|--------|---------|----------|--------|
| Customer Side | Product List Page | P0 | Users need to browse products |
| Customer Side | Product Detail Page | P0 | Users need product information |
| Customer Side | Login / Registration | P0 | User identification |
| Customer Side | Shopping Cart | P0 | Batch purchase |
| Customer Side | Submit Order | P0 | Core transaction action |
| Customer Side | Payment | P0 | Complete transaction |
| Customer Side | Order List / Details | P0 | Track order status |
| Admin Side | Product Management | P0 | List products for sale |
| Admin Side | SKU / Inventory Management | P0 | Control available stock |
| Admin Side | Order Management | P0 | Process orders |
| Admin Side | Shipment Management | P1 | Update delivery status |
| Customer Side | Search / Category Filter | P1 | Improve browsing efficiency |
| Admin Side | User Management | P2 | Future iteration |
| Customer Side | Coupons | P2 | Not required for MVP |
| Admin Side | Data Dashboard | P2 | Not needed initially |

